# Environment Setup

Create a `.env.example` file to document required environment variables:

```bash
# Google Drive OAuth2 Configuration
# Get these from https://console.cloud.google.com

# Your OAuth 2.0 Client ID
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=

# Your OAuth 2.0 Client Secret  
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=

# Redirect URI (use this exact value for desktop apps)
GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI=urn:ietf:wg:oauth:2.0:oob

# (Optional) Google Drive folder ID for syncing
# Format: https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/FOLDER_ID_HERE
GOOGLE_DRIVE_FOLDER_ID=
```

## How to Use

1. Copy this file: `cp .env.example .env`
2. Fill in your values from Google Cloud Console
3. Never commit `.env` to version control

